window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From a Pulitzer Prize finalist, \"the single most compelling, lucid, and lyrical contemporary account of the absurdity of U.S. border policy\" (</b><b><i>The Atlantic</i></b><b>). </b></p> <p>In May 2001, a group of men attempted to cross the Mexican border into the desert of southern Arizona, through the deadliest region of the continent, the \"Devil's Highway.\" Three years later, Luis Alberto Urrea wrote about what happened to them. The result was a national best seller, a Pulitzer Prize finalist, a \"book of the year\" in multiple newspapers, and a work proclaimed as a modern American classic.&nbsp;</p>"; 
